---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import HeroSection from '../components/HeroSection.astro';
---

<Layout 
    title="Frequently Asked Questions" 
    description="Find answers to common questions about mediation, arbitration, and the dispute resolution process at Aasra Arbitrix Mediation Hub LLP."
>
    <HeroSection 
        title="Frequently Asked Questions" 
        subtitle="Find answers to common questions about our dispute resolution services" 
        showButton={false}
    />
    
    <section class="section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="faq-intro">
                <p>We've compiled answers to the most common questions about our services and the dispute resolution process. If you don't find what you're looking for, please don't hesitate to <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>
            </div>
            
            <div class="faq-container">
                <div class="faq-category">
                    <h2>General Questions</h2>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>What is the difference between mediation and arbitration?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Mediation is a facilitative process where a neutral mediator helps parties communicate and negotiate to reach a voluntary agreement. The mediator does not make decisions for the parties.</p>
                            <p>Arbitration is a more formal process where an arbitrator acts similar to a judge, hearing evidence and arguments from both sides and making a binding decision (award) that resolves the dispute.</p>
                            <p>The key difference is that in mediation, the parties control the outcome, while in arbitration, the arbitrator decides the outcome.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How confidential is the dispute resolution process?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>All our dispute resolution processes are strictly confidential. This means:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Discussions during mediation or arbitration cannot be used in future legal proceedings</li>
                                <li>All documents and information shared are kept private</li>
                                <li>Our mediators and arbitrators are bound by professional confidentiality obligations</li>
                                <li>Written agreements include confidentiality clauses</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>This confidentiality creates a safe environment for open discussion and helps protect both parties' privacy and interests.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How long does the dispute resolution process take?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>The duration varies depending on the complexity of the case, the chosen resolution method, and the parties' willingness to engage in the process. Typically:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Simple mediation cases may be resolved in 1-3 sessions (2-4 weeks)</li>
                                <li>Standard cases typically take 4-8 weeks from filing to resolution</li>
                                <li>Complex cases, especially those requiring arbitration, might take 8-12 weeks</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>This timeline is significantly shorter than typical court proceedings, which can take months or years.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-category">
                    <h2>Process Questions</h2>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>Do I need a lawyer to participate in mediation or arbitration?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Having a lawyer is not required for mediation or arbitration, but it can be beneficial:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>In mediation, parties often participate without attorneys, though you may consult with one before or after sessions</li>
                                <li>In arbitration, legal representation is more common but still optional</li>
                                <li>For complex cases or significant financial/legal matters, having legal advice is recommended</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Our mediators and arbitrators are skilled at working with both represented and unrepresented parties to ensure a fair process.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>What if the other party refuses to participate?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Mediation and conciliation are voluntary processes requiring all parties' participation. If one party refuses:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>We can reach out to them to explain the benefits and address concerns</li>
                                <li>We can suggest alternative approaches that might be more acceptable</li>
                                <li>For cases with pre-existing arbitration clauses, participation may be mandatory</li>
                                <li>If efforts fail, we can advise on alternative resolution options</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Many initially reluctant parties agree to participate once they understand the process and its advantages over litigation.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>Are mediation agreements and arbitration awards legally binding?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>The legal status depends on the process:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Mediation agreements become legally binding contracts once signed by all parties</li>
                                <li>Arbitration awards are legally binding and enforceable under the Arbitration and Conciliation Act</li>
                                <li>Either can be filed with a court to add another layer of enforceability if necessary</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Our documentation process ensures that all agreements and awards meet legal requirements for enforceability.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="faq-category">
                    <h2>Practical Questions</h2>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>How much does dispute resolution cost?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Our fees vary based on the dispute resolution method, case complexity, and time required:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Initial consultation: ₹5,000</li>
                                <li>Mediation: Starting from ₹15,000 for standard cases</li>
                                <li>Arbitration: Starting from ₹30,000 for standard cases</li>
                                <li>Complex cases or those requiring specialized expertise may have higher fees</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>A detailed fee estimate is provided during the initial consultation. Though there is a cost, dispute resolution is typically 70-80% less expensive than litigation.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>Can we conduct sessions remotely?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>Yes, we offer flexible options for conducting sessions:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>In-person sessions at our office in Mumbai</li>
                                <li>Video conferencing for remote participants</li>
                                <li>Hybrid approach combining in-person and remote participation</li>
                                <li>Phone-based sessions for certain situations</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>Our virtual sessions maintain the same standards of confidentiality and professionalism as in-person meetings, making dispute resolution accessible regardless of location.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="faq-item">
                        <div class="faq-question">
                            <h3>What types of disputes can be resolved through your services?</h3>
                            <span class="faq-toggle">+</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="faq-answer">
                            <p>We handle a wide range of civil and commercial disputes, including:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Business and contract disputes</li>
                                <li>Partnership and shareholder conflicts</li>
                                <li>Family business disagreements</li>
                                <li>Property and real estate issues</li>
                                <li>Consumer disputes</li>
                                <li>Employment matters</li>
                                <li>Intellectual property conflicts</li>
                            </ul>
                            <p>However, we generally don't handle criminal matters or cases that exclusively require court determination, such as constitutional issues.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
    
    <section class="section cta-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="cta-content">
                <h2>Still Have Questions?</h2>
                <p>Contact us to schedule an initial consultation or to get answers to your specific questions.</p>
                <div class="cta-buttons">
                    <a href="/contact" class="btn btn-accent">Contact Us</a>
                    <a href="/file-case" class="btn btn-primary">File a Case</a>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>
</Layout>

<script>
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
        const faqItems = document.querySelectorAll('.faq-item');
        
        faqItems.forEach(item => {
            const question = item.querySelector('.faq-question');
            const answer = item.querySelector('.faq-answer');
            const toggle = item.querySelector('.faq-toggle');
            
            question.addEventListener('click', () => {
                const expanded = answer.classList.contains('active');
                
                // Close all answers
                document.querySelectorAll('.faq-answer').forEach(ans => {
                    ans.classList.remove('active');
                });
                document.querySelectorAll('.faq-toggle').forEach(tog => {
                    tog.textContent = '+';
                });
                
                // If clicked item was not expanded, expand it
                if (!expanded) {
                    answer.classList.add('active');
                    toggle.textContent = '−';
                }
            });
        });
    });
</script>

<style>
    .faq-intro {
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto var(--spacing-xl);
        text-align: center;
    }
    
    .faq-container {
        max-width: 900px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    
    .faq-category {
        margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
    }
    
    .faq-category h2 {
        color: var(--primary-blue);
        margin-bottom: var(--spacing-lg);
        padding-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
        border-bottom: 2px solid var(--neutral-200);
    }
    
    .faq-item {
        margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
        border: 1px solid var(--neutral-300);
        border-radius: var(--border-radius);
        overflow: hidden;
    }
    
    .faq-question {
        background-color: white;
        padding: var(--spacing-md) var(--spacing-lg);
        cursor: pointer;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: center;
    }
    
    .faq-question h3 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: 1.1rem;
        font-weight: 600;
    }
    
    .faq-toggle {
        font-size: 1.5rem;
        color: var(--primary-blue);
        font-weight: 700;
    }
    
    .faq-answer {
        padding: 0 var(--spacing-lg);
        max-height: 0;
        overflow: hidden;
        transition: max-height 0.3s ease, padding 0.3s ease;
    }
    
    .faq-answer.active {
        max-height: 1000px;
        padding: var(--spacing-md) var(--spacing-lg);
        background-color: var(--neutral-100);
    }
    
    .faq-answer p:last-child {
        margin-bottom: 0;
    }
    
    .cta-section {
        background-color: var(--primary-blue);
        color: white;
    }
    
    .cta-content {
        text-align: center;
        max-width: 800px;
        margin: 0 auto;
    }
    
    .cta-content h2 {
        color: white;
    }
    
    .cta-buttons {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: center;
        gap: var(--spacing-md);
        margin-top: var(--spacing-lg);
    }
    
    @media (max-width: 768px) {
        .faq-question h3 {
            font-size: 1rem;
        }
        
        .cta-buttons {
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            gap: var(--spacing-sm);
        }
    }
</style>